{
  "texts": [
    "In this paper, we propose OptLLM, an effective framework that augments LLMs (such as Qwen model and GPT-4) with external solvers for automated modeling and solving of optimization problems.",
    "Specifically, OptLLM comprises three modules: the interaction module for completing the problem description, the converter for translating the description into code, and the responser for calling solvers and interpreting the results, respectively.",
    "By iterating the above steps through chatting with users, OptLLM has the potential to assist both beginners and domain professionals to achieve faithful decision-making for optimization problems.",
    "We illustrate the effectiveness of OptLLM with three proof-of-concept applications and experiments.",
    "In the future, we will focus on promoting the diversity of optimization problems by including more real-world cases from various domains and scenarios."
  ]
}